=42.7.4\\n\\n## Docker Image Vulnerability Scanning\\n- Changed images between commits:\\n  - ./gradlew checkAllowedDockerImages --baseCommit=$(git rev-parse origin/master) --newCommit=$(git rev-parse HEAD)\\n- All allowed images:\\n  - ./gradlew checkAllowedDockerImages\\n\\n## Compatibility Automation (latest library versions)\\n- List libs with newer upstream versions:\\n  - ./gradlew fetchExistingLibrariesWithNewerVersions --quiet\\n- Record a newly tested version:\\n  - ./gradlew addTestedVersion -Pcoordinates=\\\"group:artifact:newVersion\\\" --lastSupportedVersion=\\\"oldVersion\\\"\\n  - Example: ./gradlew addTestedVersion -Pcoordinates=\\\"org.postgresql:postgresql:42.7.4\\\" --lastSupportedVersion=\\\"42.7.3\\\"\\n\\n## Releases and Packaging\\n- Package artifacts: ./gradlew package\\n\"}], \"isError\": false, \"timestamp\": 1777651749974}}\n../3992-8ea7ee1a/human-intervention-logs/com.h2database:h2:2.1.210/improve-library-coverage/pi-generation-2026-05-01T16-12-43-747546Z.log:207:[recv] {\"type\": \"turn_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Inspecting repository for tests**\\n\\nI need to modify some tests and check the repository. There's a requirement not to run the tests just yet, which is a bit tricky. I might need a specific skill to address missing metadata, especially since it's related to adding tests for dynamic access. It seems like AGENTS suggest reading the documentation on forge before making any changes. I should also verify if we're in the worktree root and explore the README for developing the functional spec architecture.\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_01706356aaa1fed30169f4d021f6c081959e8f80d0fc8cd69a\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABp9NAlGdlBoms4PFyTCkTi3I4wa0MIEUePhqXVuejeDC3kJPBW4cWfhLfoiYNH6Rk3RyXUelIvnHIu0XYharUzQ5NG59jeJFnfG5EXQJ34YGlCFGH085XxPeoL7zBCoVfiBJP1bQv1QrtU5iTn_2QMRcrczx9p-1ksVZr8bL_gj26qLiXeAibOsqLbyIm