 OptionHelper.instantiateByClassName(\\n                NoArgDependency.class.getName(),\\n                Dependency.class,\\n                classLoader\\n        );\\n\\n        assertThat(instance).isInstanceOf(NoArgDependency.class);\\n        assertThat(classLoader.getLoadedClassNames()).contains(NoArgDependency.class.getName());\\n    }\\n\\n    @Test\\n    void instantiateByClassNameAndParameterUsesTheMatchingPublicConstructor() throws Exception {\\n        final TrackingClassLoader classLoader = new TrackingClassLoader(OptionHelperTest.class.getClassLoader());\\n        final String expectedValue = \\\"configured-value\\\";\\n\\n        final Object instance = OptionHelper.instantiateByClassNameAndParameter(\\n                ArgumentDependency.class.getName(),\\n                Dependency.class,\\n                classLoader,\\n                String.class,\\n                expectedValue\\n        );\\n\\n        assertThat(instance).isInstanceOf(ArgumentDependency.class);\\n        assertThat(((ArgumentDependency) instance).getValue()).isEqualTo(expectedValue);\\n        assertThat(classLoader.getLoadedClassNames()).contains(ArgumentDependency.class.getName());\\n    }\\n\\n    public interface Dependency {\\n    }\\n\\n    public static final class NoArgDependency implements Dependency {\\n\\n        public NoArgDependency() {\\n        }\\n    }\\n\\n    public static final class ArgumentDependency implements Dependency {\\n\\n        private final String value;\\n\\n        public ArgumentDependency(final String value) {\\n            this.value = value;\\n        }\\n\\n        public String getValue() {\\n            return value;\\n        }\\n    }\\n\\n    private static final class TrackingClassLoader extends ClassLoader {\\n\\n        private final List<String> loadedClassNames = new ArrayList<String>();\\n\\n        private TrackingClassLoader(final ClassLoader parent) {\\n            super(parent);\\n        }\\n\\n        @Override\\n        public Class<?> loadClass(final String name) throws ClassNotFoundException {\\n            loadedClassNames.add(name);\\n            return super.loadClass(name);\\n        }\\n\\n        private List<String> getLoadedClassNames() {\\n            return loadedClassNames;\\n        }\\n    }\\n}\\n\"}], \"isError\": false, \"timestamp\": 1776966678112}]}\n/home/mihailo/git/metadata-forge/logs2/pi-generation-ch.qos.logback_logback-core_1.1.3-2026-04-23T17-52-20-371670Z.log:2249:[recv] {\"type\": \"message_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Avoiding unnecessary commits**\\n\\nI see that an untracked empty metadata file may have been generated accidentally from the workflow, which is unrelated. Since the user wants only the tests, I’ll focus on committing just the test file and the reflect-config. I’ll use git to add only those two specific paths and leave the untracked directory as is. Finally, I need to craft a commit message that clearly reflects this focus.\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_0d67ef75d26159ed0169ea5c46e7f4819fb6a80f0ee451b676\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABp6lxJJa4j965JjetuUdNXd-rtkIC7KBaWrPvsHpNE-0cUsgmCdFt7saJhoC9ioiYHQYt1osa0AKXKHbyHaRbCIbmdt35ew3rD9eoE9Gba0ihXNoDHV6ffrgn9PoDh-1utHmFIA69mjPhrHxOWmBGmh1IqHllTbox1YA3zqOcSwn6Lq42W-wj6gT92ulzXt2p3wZYqNBUen1Tg8EehskBNh-g_9iHY8rh0DN319zfPKRCktrgsnU1MNppKMMjFNb7aCvK4qw_m5RV-O0AHkG-Tbc3VG1eBFgzwAojM6uocEuslITphBgBk7LVq8t42Zp80YZpZGWEnNJG_Vi0PFGyi0HWma2246AAyjAUK4YSnZzauoZgZgb7hrEp5kT2zzrqGQabL3g741m8eeLZzP3_ZCRwDBQYr5nemhJyFHSVR-m4IJtJWtnndT_yDus_lOv6sccVKg2LwTmCx71eoac2olq6H2KTR0p5yS8PunVJff9peTtEkA2Rv5ZbImy0TclAtfnkTAvCpiJTZoyQumXLoOuAxm0-FPVUAFjhMcBycQb4bwSIYrXJlzHUR7bGmjGl11pve61QZWs4KNGhfzDgfxnG3Z4WxOsAB1ZvlZPFP2fS-iTmMk6nZ7ZZYdxFZmaKtSlTiBXSQRzpAACplMZXCEXfPzrR4awkWWGIwu-l0FIMq3JVJVJgddAi4ZD2bFAu1E31gZQ44HT9lFF4GiKRye3No8kDNHUgIg24zk0vpp3ZCRLT7O8JaDQB9HlqFHLyn0nkxH11h09rf2q27RDoL