op` / X11 JNI metadata. This lines up with the stalled dynamic-access report (`84/101`, 83.17%).\n\nPlease inspect:\n- `logs/com.h2database:h2:2.1.210/metadata-fix/codex.log`\n- `logs/com.h2database:h2:2.1.210/native-test-verify/cycle-39-runNativeTraceImage-2026-05-04T13-49-51-366010Z.log`\n- `logs/com.h2database:h2:2.1.210/native-test-verify/cycle-38-runNativeTraceImage-2026-05-04T13-48-05-460445Z.log`\n- `human-intervention-logs/com.h2database:h2:2.1.210/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-04T12-35-43-699171Z.log`\n- `human-intervention-logs/com.h2database:h2:2.1.210/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-04T12-37-33-490065Z.log`\n\nNext steps:\n1. Review or remove the generated `ServerTest` path that exercises `Server.openBrowser`, since it appears to drag in `java.desktop` / X11 behavior that is not converging in Native Image.\n2. Narrow the `JdbcUtils` / `DatabaseMetaData` coverage tests so they exercise H2-owned behavior without forcing broad `java.sql.DatabaseMetaData` reflective coverage one method at a time.\n3. Re-run the H2 JVM + native trace verification on the preserved branch and keep only changes that converge without introducing more `java.desktop` / `sun.java2d.*` registrations."}}
